# Component in std::path - Rust

```
pub enum Component<'a> {
    Prefix(PrefixComponent<'a>),
    RootDir,
    CurDir,
    ParentDir,
    Normal(&'a OsStr),
}
```

Expand description

A single component of a path.

A `Component` roughly corresponds to a substring between path separators (`/` or `\`).

This `enum` is created by iterating over [`Components`](struct.Components.html "struct std::path::Components"), which in turn is created by the [`components`](about:blank/struct.Path.html#method.components "method std::path::Path::components") method on [`Path`](struct.Path.html "struct std::path::Path").

## [§](#examples)Examples

```
use std::path::{Component, Path};

let path = Path::new("/tmp/foo/bar.txt");
let components = path.components().collect::<Vec<_>>();
assert_eq!(&components, &[
    Component::RootDir,
    Component::Normal("tmp".as_ref()),
    Component::Normal("foo".as_ref()),
    Component::Normal("bar.txt".as_ref()),
]);
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++use+std::path::%7BComponent,+Path%7D;%0A++++%0A++++let+path+=+Path::new(%22/tmp/foo/bar.txt%22);%0A++++let+components+=+path.components().collect::%3CVec%3C_%3E%3E();%0A++++assert_eq!(%26components,+%26%5B%0A++++++++Component::RootDir,%0A++++++++Component::Normal(%22tmp%22.as_ref()),%0A++++++++Component::Normal(%22foo%22.as_ref()),%0A++++++++Component::Normal(%22bar.txt%22.as_ref()),%0A++++%5D);%0A%7D&edition=2021)

[§](#variant.Prefix)1.0.0

A Windows path prefix, e.g., `C:` or `\\server\share`.

There is a large variety of prefix types, see [`Prefix`](enum.Prefix.html "enum std::path::Prefix")’s documentation for more.

Does not occur on Unix.

[§](#variant.RootDir)1.0.0

The root directory component, appears after any prefix and before anything else.

It represents a separator that designates that a path starts from root.

[§](#variant.CurDir)1.0.0

A reference to the current directory, i.e., `.`.

[§](#variant.ParentDir)1.0.0

A reference to the parent directory, i.e., `..`.

[§](#variant.Normal)1.0.0

A normal component, e.g., `a` and `b` in `a/b`.

This variant is the most common one, it represents references to files or directories.

use std::path::Path;

let components: Vec<_> = path.components().map(|comp| comp.as_os_str()).collect();
assert_eq!(&components, &[".", "tmp", "foo", "bar.txt"]);
